<tool-use data-tool-type="mcp" data-tool-name="mcp_playwrightMCP_browser_evaluate">
<details>
          <summary>Tool use: **mcp_playwrightMCP_browser_evaluate**</summary>
      
*Called tool*: playwrightMCP - browser_evaluate: Evaluate JavaScript expression on page or element

*Parameters*:
  * function: async () => {
  const response = await fetch('http://localhost:3000/api/attendance/monthly?employeeId=000001&year=2025&month=12');
  const data = await response.json();
  const today = new Date().toISOString().split('T')[0];
  return {
    today: today,
    dailyDataCount: data.dailyData ? data.dailyData.length : 0,
    todayRecord: data.dailyData ? data.dailyData.find(d => d.WORK_DATE === today) : null,
    recentRecords: data.dailyData ? data.dailyData.slice(-5).map(d => ({
      date: d.WORK_DATE,
      clockIn: d.CLOCK_IN_TIME,
      clockOut: d.CLOCK_OUT_TIME
    })) : []
  };
}

*Result*:
### Result

  "today": "2025-12-08",
  "dailyDataCount": 0,
  "recentRecords": []
}
